										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p class="has-luminous-vivid-amber-background-color has-background"><strong>Summary:</strong> Homeopathic Treatment for Viral Fever uses remedies like Aconitum Napellus, Belladonna, Gelsemium and Eupatorium Perfoliatum depending on the signs.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">What is Viral Fever?</h2>



<p>Viral fever is another form of fever that results from a virus that has attacked and is being fought by the body&#8217;s systems. It happens when viruses get into our cells, replicate and the body temperature rises in response to the infection that triggers the immune system. </p>



<p>Typical signs of viral fever include fever, shivering, joint pains, weakness, and in some instances, throat inflammation or coughing. The fever can be quite low, ranging between 99°F or 37.2°C and very high, including 103°F or 39.4°C depending on the virus causing the flu.</p>



<p>Viral fevers may occur due to flu, cold, or some serious diseases like <a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/how-to-treat-dengue-fever-with-homeopathy"   title="dengue fever" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked"  data-wpil-monitor-id="2681">dengue fever</a>. Such fevers usually only come for a few days and can be relieved by getting plenty of rest and water and taking some pain relievers. One must see a doctor if they or their child develops symptoms or if symptoms are severe, as some viral infections need specific management.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Symptoms of Viral Fever</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Fatigue and Weakness:</strong> Some people feel very exhausted and sleepy most of the time.</li>



<li><strong>Body Aches and Headaches:</strong> Discomfort, such as muscle and joint pain, are very common amongst the older people.</li>



<li><strong><a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/how-to-treat-sore-throat-with-homeopathy"   title="Sore Throat" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked"  data-wpil-monitor-id="2680">Sore Throat</a> and Cough:</strong> These symptoms are often seen and are especially common during respiratory viral illnesses.</li>



<li><strong>Nasal Congestion:</strong> It is usually experienced in colds and flu, and when the throat is irritated, you might experience a runny or blocked nose.</li>



<li><strong>Gastrointestinal Issues:</strong> Some people will get a feeling of nausea, vomiting, or <a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/how-to-treat-diarrhea-with-homeopathy"   title="diarrhea" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked"  data-wpil-monitor-id="2687">diarrhea</a>.</li>



<li><strong><a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/how-to-treat-skin-rashes-with-homeopathy"   title="Skin Rash" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked"  data-wpil-monitor-id="2683">Skin Rash</a>: </strong>Some viral illnesses cause a rash on the<strong> </strong>skin.</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Causes of Viral Fever</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Respiratory Infections:</strong> The flu virus and the rhinovirus are ordinary viruses that cause flu and the common <a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/how-to-treat-cold-with-homeopathy"   title="cold" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked"  data-wpil-monitor-id="2692">cold</a><strong>,</strong> respectively.</li>



<li><strong>Gastrointestinal Viruses:</strong> Viral fever associated with norovirus and rotavirus may present with additional symptoms of nausea, <a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/how-to-treat-vomiting-with-homeopathy"   title="vomiting" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked"  data-wpil-monitor-id="2691">vomiting</a> and diarrhea.</li>



<li><span style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;"><strong>Arboviruses:</strong> These are acquired through bites from insects, with the following being examples: dengue fever and Zika virus, and these are most common in the tropical region.</span></li>



<li><span style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;"><strong>Childhood Viral Infections:</strong> Conditions that give rise to viral fever include measles, mumps, and rubella. However, vaccination can help prevent it.</span></li>



<li><strong>Hepatitis Viruses:</strong> These affect the liver and can cause conditions such as viral fever together with common symptoms like yellowness of the skin.</li>



<li><span style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;"><strong>Contact with Infected Bodily Fluids:</strong> There are viruses that are transmitted through affected human body fluids, which infect the body with fever.</span></li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Does Homeopathy for Viral Fever Work?</h3>



<p>Homeopathy can be very effective in managing viral fever. Therefore, homeopathic remedies also treat the cause of fever and relieve the conditions that may accompany it, thus making it safe. Anti-viral preparations include Gelsemium, Bryonia, and <a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/arsenicum-album-uses"   title="Arsenicum Album" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked"  data-wpil-monitor-id="2689">Arsenicum Album</a>. They work to bring down fever, remove body pains, and boost the body’s immune response. </p>



<p>Homeopathic Treatment for Viral Fever works on the basis of an individual&#8217;s suffering and his general health condition so it gives a more rapid cure without any side effects which normal medicines have. Most patients using homeopathic treatments show that they not only assist in the treatment of fever but also enhance general patient health. To get the best results from homeopathic treatment, one should see a qualified homeopathic doctor.</p>



