<li><strong>Coccus cacti</strong>: Good for coughs that result in a thick, stringy type of sputum that is difficult to cough up. Generally, the situation worsens during warm conditions.</li>



<li><strong><a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/belladonna-uses"   title="Belladonna" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked"  data-wpil-monitor-id="2513">Belladonna</a></strong>: When given as a treatment, it is administered in the first stages of whooping cough, where symptoms include dry barking coughs, sore throat, and fever. Other symptoms may range from facial redness, a pounding <a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/how-to-treat-headache-with-homeopathy"   title="headache" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked"  data-wpil-monitor-id="2516">headache</a>, and making you sensitive to light.</li>



<li><strong><a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/antimonium-tartaricum-uses"   title="Antimonium tartaricum" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked"  data-wpil-monitor-id="2512">Antimonium tartaricum</a></strong>: For wheezing cough, chest-clearing rattle, shortness of breath, or sudden difficulty in breathing. Coughing can make patients feel a littleæweak and tired.</li>



<li><strong>Cuprum metallicum</strong>: Especially for those cases of cough that are spasmodic or that is accompanied by <a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/how-to-treat-breathlessness-with-homeopathy"   title="breathlessness" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked"  data-wpil-monitor-id="2518">breathlessness</a>. It treats occasional and severe coughing bouts.</li>



<li><strong><a class="wpil_keyword_link" href="https://weclinic.in/blog/ipecacuanha-uses"   title="Ipecacuanha" data-wpil-keyword-link="linked"  data-wpil-monitor-id="2509">Ipecacuanha</a></strong>: Suitable to use when you are having a cough that is followed by nausea or gagging. It also relieves breathlessness and throat constriction, plus other conditions that cause coughing with excess phlegm.</li>



<li><strong>Carbo vegetabilis</strong>: Prescribed for severe fatigue or exhaustion common after paroxysms of coughing. Some might include difficulty in breathing or agonal respiration and cyanosis, especially around the lips or nails.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Homeopathic Treatment for Whooping Cough in Children</h3>



